The paper proposes a meta learning method for video summarization, which involves both computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely categories. Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of deep neural networks (DNNs) and backpropagation, which are common in multimedia (MM) and artificial intelligence (AI) research. Finally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) in terms of summarizing video content.
